graph TD
    A[Effect of land use on<br/>local precipitation]
    A --> B[Data collection<br/>Rainfall data + land use data]
    B --> C[Rainfall<br/>Continuous variable]
    B --> D[Land use<br/>Discrete variable]
    C --> E[Probability & distribution<br/>Normal or Gamma distribution fit?]
    D --> E
    E --> F[Moments<br/>Mean, variance, skewness, kurtosis]
    E --> G[Quantile function<br/>1-in-10-year extreme rainfall]
    F --> H[Key analysis<br/>Urban vs rural: temporal-seasonal]
    G --> H
    H --> I[Correlation methods<br/>Pearson correlation<br/>Multiple linear regression<br/>Independent samples t-test]
    H --> J[Clustering methods<br/>K-means clustering<br/>Cluster 1: High rain, low urbanisation<br/>Cluster 2: Low rain, high urbanisation]
    I --> K[Expected outcomes<br/>Correlation between urbanisation and rainfall<br/>Local-scale effects quantified<br/>Relationship strength via statistical metrics]
    J --> K


    %% Classes
    class A primary;
    class B,E,H secondary;
    class C variable;
    class D variableAlt;
    class F,G neutral;
    class I methods;
    class J cluster;
    class K outcome;


